<HEADLINE>
FT  03 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Falcon declines
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A drop in pre-tax profits, from Pounds 175,000 to Pounds 72,000, was
announced by Falcon, the pipeline distributor, for the half year to
end-September.
Turnover fell to Pounds 2.88m (Pounds 3.15m) partly because of the loss of
some contracts to the water industry. The interim dividend is cut to 2.5p
(3p), payable from earnings of 2.5p (5.3p) per share.
