FT  03 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Cox Insurance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Cox, a Lloyd's agency, and Raphael Zorn Hemsley, the stockbrokers, have
raised Pounds 12m for a new company to invest in the insurance market next
year.
The launch of Cox Insurance Holdings means the total extra corporate
investment in Lloyd's this year may now exceed Pounds 350m. This is in
addition to the Pounds 900m invested last year. The new company hopes to be
listed on the stock exchange next year.
