FT  03 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Scantronic appoints advisers
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PAUL TAYLOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Scantronic Holdings, the security components group, which has become the
subject of growing bid speculation in recent months, yesterday appointed
Samuel Montague as its financial adviser.
Scantronic said it would need the advice 'particularly in relation to the
unsolicited approaches received'. It also announced it was appointing Norton
Rose as legal adviser.
A number of companies have announced their interest in making a bid although
the company has declined to identify its other suitors.
Scantronic has appeared increasingly vulnerable over the past year. In July
it announced the departure of its finance director, Mr Ray Dias, claiming
that he had failed to alert the board to the twin impact of increased
borrowing and difficult trading conditions.
