<HEADLINE>
FT  03 DEC 94 / UK Company News: C&amp;G members can vote on March 31
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALISON SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The 1m-plus members of Cheltenham &amp; Gloucester Building Society, the UK's
sixth largest society, will be able to vote on the proposed cash bid for the
society by Lloyds Bank on Friday March 31, C&amp;G said yesterday.
The special meeting will be held at the London Arena, which holds about
12,000.
A transfer statement, giving details of the plans, will be sent out to
members in the last week of February. It will include the 1994 results for
both C&amp;G and Lloyds, which are likely to have been announced that month.
The transfer has to be agreed by separate votes of investors and of
borrowers. Under building societies' legislation, not all of them are
eligible for a share of the Pounds 1.8bn cash bid by Lloyds.
A simple majority of borrowers taking part in the vote is enough to pass
their resolution, but the investors' resolution must be passed by both 75
per cent of those voting and 50 per cent of those eligible to vote in the
case of the investors' resolution.
If members approve the deal, then C&amp;G will become part of the Lloyds Bank
group on August 1.
Cash payments to eligible investors and depositors are expected to be made
soon after that. C&amp;G estimates that the average total payment to an
individual will be about Pounds 2,000.
</TEXT>
