<HEADLINE>
FT  03 DEC 94 / Ex-Brent Walker man must pay fine
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mr Wilfred Aquilina, the former finance director at Brent Walker, was
yesterday told he must pay a Pounds 25,000 fine for false accounting, even
though he pleaded poverty.
The judge, Mr Geoffrey Rivlin, refused to accept that Mr Aquilina was
insolvent.
He told him at Southwark Crown Court: 'To suggest that you can't afford to
pay is an affront to common sense and to the many people who are in a far
worse position than you to pay a fine.'
The fine was imposed three weeks ago in addition to a suspended sentence,
but an adjournment was granted for a special investigation into Mr
Aquilina's financial circumstances. Yesterday the judge extended from six
months to a year the period in which Mr Aquilina had to pay.
