FT  03 DEC 94 / Magistrate to question Alcatel Alsthom chief
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A magistrate investigating alleged overbilling of state-owned France Telecom
plans to summon Mr Pierre Suard, chairman of French industrial giant Alcatel
Alsthom, for questioning, an official said yesterday. The news followed the
release earlier in the day of Mr Pierre Guichet, chairman of Alcatel's
telecommunications unit CIT, after two weeks in a Paris jail. Mr Guichet,
62, had received the full support of Alcatel CIT which expressed outrage at
his incarceration without charge. He remains under investigation.
Mr Guichet was ordered jailed by investigating magistrate Jean-Marie d'Huy
who is looking into the allegations that Alcatel CIT overcharged France
Telecom, its biggest customer, by an estimated FFr2bn (Pounds 230m). Alcatel
CIT has consistently rejected the allegations, saying there had been a
misunderstanding of its billing practices. The official said that Mr Suard,
head of parent Alcatel Alsthom, would be called in for questioning during
December. In July, Mr d'Huy placed Mr Suard under investigation on suspicion
of underpaying for security measures at his current and previous residences.
He was briefly arrested and questioned for 12 hours in July by the police
fraud squad.
