<TEXT>
IRI, the Italian state holding company, has fixed a deadline of December 12
for potential buyers to present their bids for Ilva Laminati Pianti, the
flat steel subsidiary of Italy's state-owned steel producer.
IRI is attempting to strike a deal for ILP by the end of 1994. If it fails,
Italy will fall foul of the European Commission, which has to enforce an EU
