coal-handling systems, are sold to Indonesia's public sector.
In 1992 Bukaka exported its first passenger boarding bridge and since then
it has sold bridges to airports in Japan, Thailand and Singapore.
Mr Sadel Muhammad, president and chief executive officer, said that Bukaka
would continue to target Asia-Pacific economies and step up exports of oil
and gas equipment, transmission towers and bulk-handling systems.
Bukaka's net profit last year was Rp9.1bn (Dollars 4.2m) on sales of
Rp151bn.
This year the company expects a net profit of Rp15.4bn.
