<HEADLINE>
FT  02 DEC 94 / International Company News: Barlo midterm fall to IPounds
1.81m
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Barlo, the Dublin-based radiators and packaging group, blamed lower margins
in its plastics business for a fall in pre-tax profits for the six months to
September 30 from IPounds 2.42m to IPounds 1.81m (Pounds 1.78m).
Turnover rose to IPounds 55.5m (IPounds 43.4m) reflecting continued organic
growth and the contribution from Veha Radiators.
Earnings per share were 1.02p (1.76p) and the interim dividend is unchanged
at 0.4p.
