<HEADLINE>
FT  02 DEC 94 / Locals denounce free trade
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BOGOTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Latin American indigenous leaders have denounced free trade as a scourge for
their land and people, as government officials from the 34 countries
scheduled to attend next week's Summit of the Americas negotiate last-minute
agreements on trade issues. Signed by representatives of more than 8m
indigenous people in South and Central America, the letter said free trade
would benefit multinational corporations at their expense and 'reinforce the
economic dominion' of the US.
