FT  02 DEC 94 / World Trade News: Hopes for growth hormone
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By HILARY BARNES
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COPENHAGEN
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Novo Nordisk, the Danish pharmaceuticals producer, hopes to be able to begin
commercial sales of its growth hormone in the US early next year. This
statement was made after the US International Trade Commission dismissed
complaints by Genentech, the US bio-tech group, that Novo Nordisk's product
infringed Genentech patents. The Danish company said it already marketed the
growth hormone, known as Norditropin in 50 countries.
