FT  02 DEC 94 / Australian company case fails
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By NIKKI TAIT
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   SYDNEY
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Charges filed by the Australian Securities Commission against Mr Robert
Champion de Crespigny, head of the Normandy Poseidon resources group and one
of the most prominent figures in Australia's mining industry, and Mr Thomas
Meiklejohn, a former Normandy employee, were yesterday dismissed in the
Melbourne courts.
