de Crespigny and Mr Meiklejohn, while chairman and managing director
respectively of Brunswick, a small mining company, that took over Bendigo
Gold, had failed to take reasonable steps to ensure that a statement to
shareholders did not contain misleading information. At the heart of the
matter was the valuation of certain mining interests.
