<HEADLINE>
FT  01 DEC 94 / Survey of Software at Work - Winter 1994 (11): Speed is
essential - Ease of use for small businesses / Claire Gooding finds that
moving rapidly from pub to pub poses accounting problems for Adams Inns
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CLAIRE GOODING
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A small family business run from home, Adams Inns specialises in being a
'locum' for the pub trade. The quick turnover of pubs brings some specific
accounting problems.
Adams specialises in running pubs, most of them from the Tetley Brewery,
taking over the administration between long-term tenants. One of its tasks
as a 'locum' is often to build up the trade of a pub that has become run
down or neglected, although it also runs two long-term leases at present.
Its tally of pubs fluctuates - it currently has six - and for every pub it
takes on, it has to set up accounting details and administration, providing
full accounts when it hands it back to the brewery or on to new tenants.
In a constant state of data take-on, there are few software products that
would not present headaches.
'We have to be able to set up very rapidly. We looked at Pegasus Opera, and
found it very powerful, but a lot of these packages need a PhD to run them,'
says Ian Napier, development manager of Adams Inns. 'We found it was taking
two days to set up the nominals for each individual cost centre.'
A chance encounter with the managing director of a software house led to led
to a free trial of a package called WinAccs. Mr Napier had previously used
the WinBuild property development accounting package from the same stable,
FCG, and was delighted to find the same ease of use in its general-purpose
offshoot, WinAccs, using Windows.
'With WinAccs it takes 15 seconds to set up the nominals. We didn't need
training because of the incredibly friendly front end. We bought the package
and had the entire lot loaded in two days,' Mr Napier explains. Once the
coding structure was set up using an external consultant, Adams had a
'skeleton' that could be applied to every pub. The reporting structures were
also tailored to provide the required management information.
With WinAccs Mr Napier found an easy solution to the problem of folio
numbers for tracking invoices, (which would have needed a costly Pounds
2,500 conversion on the previous package), and also found a speedy response
from FCG when he had a printer problem - the kind that dogs all SoHo (small
office home office) sites. 'It took two calls, one to report it, one to fix
it.
'One of the best things about FCG is its fantastic support. You can talk
straight to the developers if you need to, but we've had no reliability
problems. Upgrades arrive like clockwork, and they are easy to install.
'If there are any disadvantages, it is that because it is so invitingly easy
to use, we made some mistakes in the initial analysis of the sub-schedules.
We should have had a professional accountant in earlier, to help us set up
some of the postings and allocations.'
Adams is now an enthusiastic user of the FCG integrated modules for payroll
and job costing, all run on one Fujistu 486 PC (with optical drive), which
also supports another home-based business. The total cost of all the
software modules was Pounds 700, a special trade-in price for Pegasus Opera,
plus a year's maintenance.
Supplier profile Product: WinAccs, launched in 1988, is a Windows-based
accounting system for the provision of financial information to small
companies.
The package is integrated with a Windows-based payroll package, WinPay, and
software for job costing.
Suppliers: FCG Computer Systems is a privately owned UK company founded in
1975 to provide software products for the construction industry, and claims
to be the first in the world to have developed an accounting package under
Windows.
Turnover: Pounds 3m in 1993, profit about Pounds 150,000.
Employees: 50 in the UK only.
Number of users: 1,500 in the UK.
Price: Pounds 495 for single user. Typical configuration (Sales, Purchase,
Nominal ledgers, Cashbook, Data Extraction, Sales Invoicing and report
Generator) Pounds 995.
Hardware and operating systems: IBM PC and compatible, under Windows 3.1.
Sales and support/ maintenance: direct for FCG, Pounds 99 annual fee
includes upgrades and legislation changes.
Other services available: training, consultancy, project management.
User views: easy to use, minimum training, excellent responsive support,
continual upgrades.
Contact: Bob Childs, FCG.
Tel: 0442 876601.
</TEXT>
